Data reflects budget figures in light of Decree Number 88 for the year 2024.

The notable increase in tax revenues is mainly in light of the recovery in economic activity, and enhancing foreign currency availability, in addition to the effect of the digitalization of tax system on enhancing tax collections, and widening the tax base.

Enhancing the efficiency of public spending during the period of study mainly throug efforts  to enhance debt management via allocating interest payments burdens along the fiscal year, and diversifying sources of finances, while enhancing ceiling on the unified treasury accounts. In addition, public investment spending has been reduced to align with the government decision of  enacting identified ceiling on public investments.
# Revised, subject to further revision in light of final accounts.
1/ Includes Interest and Principal Payments (excluding arrears).
2/ It is noteworthy that final accounts of the state budget 2015/2016  is still under review by the Parliament and will remain preliminary until being approved.
